          <p class='first-para'>
            I was about to conclude my remarks in response to the noble Baroness, Lady Miller of Chilthorne Domer. I felt that, for a community interest, it is probably more beneficial to conduct certain aspects of the system in parallel, rather than wait for a long inquiry which, like the Sizewell B inquiry, can last several years, through all of which a lawyer has to be retained. I therefore do not think there is any disadvantage in this respect to community
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_190gc' title='Col. 190GC &mdash; HL Deb 01 March 2004 vol 658 c190GC' name='column_190gc' href='#column_190gc' rel='bookmark'>190GC</a>
            groups and those with limited resources. I think that it will speed up the process while not diminishing the degree of engagement by all those with an interest who are rightly provided for in the planning process.
